# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SAFETY FIRST: never commit data, images, or model weights.
# This repo is public. The datasets it audits are not — medical imaging data is
# typically governed by a data-use agreement that forbids redistribution, and a
# single committed frame is a real breach that git history makes permanent.
# Audit inputs (manifest CSV, features .npy) stay local. Code ships; data never.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# medical images / any image
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.bmp
*.tif
*.tiff
*.dcm
*.nii
*.nii.gz
*.svs
*.mp4
*.avi

# datasets, manifests, extracted features, arrays
data/
datasets/
*.csv
*.tsv
*.npy
*.npz
*.h5
*.hdf5
*.parquet
*.pkl
*.pickle

# model weights / checkpoints
*.pth
*.pt
*.ckpt
*.onnx
*.safetensors
checkpoints/
runs/
wandb/

# audit outputs (may embed dataset specifics)
report.txt
report.html
outputs/
figures/

# credentials — never, under any circumstance
.env
*.pem
*.key
secrets*
credentials*

# internal working material: planning docs, pre-submission checklists.
# These name the internal project/dataset and local paths; they are deliberately
# not published. NOTE: HTML comments are NOT hidden on GitHub — do not "hide"
# internal notes inside a published file, put them here.
_internal/

# python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.eggs/
.venv/
venv/
env/
miccai_env/
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# os / editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/

# demo/ is generated by tutorial/make_demo.py — never commit its outputs
tutorial/demo/
